FoLogic-fw-keil - Installation Guide
=====================================

FoLogic-fw is a project based on the Keil C51 IDE. 

Prerequisites
-------------

- [Keil C51](https://www.keil.com/c51/) (uVision IDE)
- Cypress EZ-USB FX2LP development tools

Build Steps
-----------

1. Launch Keil uVision
2. Open `FoLogic.uvproj` from the project root directory
3. Select **Project → Build Target** (or press F7)
4. After successful compilation, the output files will be found in the `Output/` directory:
   - `FoLogic.fw`    - Firmware image for Cypress FX2
   - `FoLogic.iic`   - I2C EEPROM image for boot loading
   - `FoLogic.hex`   - Intel HEX format

Programming
-----------

Use a Cypress FX2 programming tool (such as CyConsole or Cypress Suite USB) 
to download the firmware to the device.

- **RAM loading:** Load `FoLogic.fw` directly into the FX2 RAM via USB.
- **EEPROM burning:** Write `FoLogic.iic` to an I2C EEPROM for 
  stand-alone boot (the FX2 will auto-load from EEPROM on power-up).
